@dev State Constants
 DRAFT = the expense is added, possibly with missing info
 SUBMITTED = submitted to the OB for review, all precoditions are met
 SUBMITTED_WITH_EXCEPTION = submitted expense does not meet all preconditions
 REVIEWED = the OB has reviewed the invoice
 NEEDS_UPDATE = the OB has sent the invoice back to the CFP for modification
 APPROVED = VDB approves the invoice out of REVIEWED
 REJECTED = VDB (or DGD) rejects the invoice out of reviewed (a comment is required)
 FORCE_APPROVED = VDB approves the invoice out of REVIEWED even of it is not ok

documentation.text:
@notice Generate state machine DID
 @param fsmIndex state machine index
@title Expense Contract
Expense Events

@dev State Constants
 DRAFT = the expense is added, possibly with missing info
 SUBMITTED = submitted to the OB for review, all precoditions are met
 SUBMITTED_WITH_EXCEPTION = submitted expense does not meet all preconditions
 REVIEWED = the OB has reviewed the invoice
 NEEDS_UPDATE = the OB has sent the invoice back to the CFP for modification
 APPROVED = VDB approves the invoice out of REVIEWED
 REJECTED = VDB (or DGD) rejects the invoice out of reviewed (a comment is required)
 FORCE_APPROVED = VDB approves the invoice out of REVIEWED even of it is not ok
@dev Role Constants
Expense states
@dev Expense roles

@dev Expense helper role collection
 specifies anyone who can edit an exponse

@notice Returns all possible states

@notice Generate state machine DID
 @param fsmIndex state machine index

params.callForTenders: IPFS hash of the call for tenders document

params.tenderResponse: IPFS hash of the tender response document

params.tenderSelectionArgumentation: IPFS hash of the tender selection document

params.toState: state where we are transitioning to

params.ipfsFieldContainerHash: IPFS hash of the metadata fields

params.callForTenders: IPFS hash of the call for tenders document
params.fsmIndex: registry index of the statemachine struct
params.ipfsFieldContainerHash: IPFS hash of the metadata fields

getIndexLength().details: Returns the length of the state machine registry

returns.length: the number of state machines in the registry

params.revisorComment: IPFS hash of the revisor comment document

params.uiFieldDefinitionsHash: IPFS hash containing the UI field definitions JSON

transitionState(uint256,bytes32).details: Ensures predefined transition criteria are met before transitioning to a new state. Executes callbacks. Emits a Transition event after a successful transition.

params.fsmIndex: registry index of the transitioning state machine
params.toState: identifier of the state to transition to

STATE_DRAFT.details: State Constants DRAFT = the expense is added, possibly with missing info SUBMITTED = submitted to the OB for review, all precoditions are met SUBMITTED_WITH_EXCEPTION = submitted expense does not meet all preconditions REVIEWED = the OB has reviewed the invoice NEEDS_UPDATE = the OB has sent the invoice back to the CFP for modification APPROVED = VDB approves the invoice out of REVIEWED REJECTED = VDB (or DGD) rejects the invoice out of reviewed (a comment is required) FORCE_APPROVED = VDB approves the invoice out of REVIEWED even of it is not ok

_canEdit.details: Expense helper role collection specifies anyone who can edit an exponse

_index.details: The index is a collection of DIDs for every state machine in the registry Usually the getIndex call returns a list of contract addresses however as FSMs are uniquely identified by their DID we return those instead

_meta.details: StateMachineMeta contains meta data for every StateMachine - seeing as struct are not composable and the base StateMachine struct is defined in the FiniteStateMachine abstract there's no other way to compose structs than having two separte arrays where the indices match.Mint is aware of the above and will zip these two into a single struct so statemachines from the outside will look as a composition of both StateMachine and StateMachineMeta structs.

_upgradeableRegistry.details: The address of the upgradeable registry this contract belongs to. Note that both this property together with the UPGRADEABLE_REGISTRY_TARGET const define a contract that is part of an upgradeable registry and provides the link to the registry if required.

addCallForTendersDocumentation(uint256,s.notice: Add call for tenders IPFS hash

addTenderResponse(uint256,string).notice: Add tender response document IPFS hash

addTenderSelectionArgumentation(uint256,.notice: Add tender selection document IPFS hash

canBeSubmitted(uint256,bytes32,bytes32).notice: Returns whether an expense can be submitted or not

getAllowedFunctionsForState(bytes32).notice: Returns method signatures for functions which are allowed to execute in the given state

getAllowedRolesForState(bytes32).notice: Retrieve all roles that are allowed to move it to the given state

getByIndex(uint256).notice: Returns the structs composing a statemachine for given index

getCallbacksForState(bytes32).notice: Returns method signatures for functions that will get called after transitioning to the given state

getContents().notice: Returns all state machines structs in a single fetch

getIndexLength().notice: Returns the length of the state machine registry

getNextStatesForState(bytes32).notice: Retrieve all possible next states for a certain state

getPreFunctionForState(bytes32).notice: Returns method signatures for functions that need to be called before transitioning to the given state

getPreconditionsForState(bytes32).notice: Returns method signatures for functions that act as preconditions that must be met in order to transition to the given state

getUIFieldDefinitionsHash().notice: Returns the UI field definition hash

recordRevisorComment(uint256,string).notice: Add revisor comment document IPFS hash

setUIFieldDefinitionsHash(string).notice: Set the UI field definition hash

transitionState(uint256,bytes32).notice: Transitions a state machine to a new state
